;B[no]LB[gr:A]C[Correct. White's eye shape is incomplete and White still owes Black a move at A. 

Later, if Black plays A, he can try to capture White, but Black needs to either be alive first, or have 10 liberties to win a capturing race. 

White's liberty count after A, H1, H2 is: 8 liberties for the 5 space big eye, -1 for the stone at H2, +2 external liberties = 9 liberties and sente. Note that Black can exchange E1 for F1 in sente, because it threatens to collapse White's big eye into a four shape. So you should assume E1 and F1 have already been played when counting liberties in this case.]))
